# defining number of clusters to split the data into
def clusters(data, max_k):
    means= []
    inertias=[]
    for k in range(1,max_k):
        kmeans=KMeans(n_clusters=k)
        kmeans.fit(data)
        means.append(k)
        inertias.append(kmeans.inertia_)
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 5))
    ax.plot(means, inertias, 'o-')
    ax.set_xlabel('Number of clusters')
    ax.set_ylabel('Inertia')
    ax.set_title('Elbow plot')
    ax.grid(True)
    plt.show()

In [36]:
# defining a z-score threshold to identify outliers
z_score_threshold = 2

# defining a function to mark outliers based on z-scores
def mark_zscore_outliers(df, column, threshold):
    df[f'{column}_outlier'] = df[column] > threshold

# applying outlier detection for each party
for party in ['apc_outliers', 'lp_outliers', 'pdp_outliers', 'nnpp_outliers']:
    mark_zscore_outliers(location, party, z_score_threshold)

# Creating a folium map centered around the mean location of all polling units
map_center = [location['Latitude'].mean(), location['Longitude'].mean()]
lagos_map = folium.Map(location=map_center, zoom_start=12)

# defining colors for clusters and outliers
cluster_colors = {0: 'blue', 1: 'green', 2: 'purple'}
party_colors = {'apc_outliers': 'red', 'lp_outliers': 'pink', 'pdp_outliers': 'orange', 'nnpp_outliers': 'black'}

# adding markers for all polling units and grouping in clusters using cluster_colors to lagos_map
for _, row in location.iterrows():
    folium.Marker(
        location=[row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']],
        tooltip=f"Unit: {row['new_puname']}, Cluster: {row['cluster_no']}, Ward: {row['ward']}",
        icon=folium.Icon(color=cluster_colors[row['cluster_no']], icon='info-sign')
    ).add_to(lagos_map)

# defining a function to add markers for the highest outliers and handle multiple outliers
def add_outlier_markers(df):
    highest_outliers = pd.DataFrame()
    
    # Find the highest outlier for each ward and party
    for party in ['apc_outliers', 'lp_outliers', 'pdp_outliers', 'nnpp_outliers']:
        party_outliers = df[df[f'{party}_outlier']]
        highest_outliers_party = party_outliers.groupby('ward').apply(lambda x: x.loc[x[party].idxmax()]).reset_index(drop=True)
        highest_outliers_party['party'] = party
        highest_outliers = pd.concat([highest_outliers, highest_outliers_party], ignore_index=True)

    # identifying polling units with multiple party outliers
    multi_party_outliers = highest_outliers.groupby('new_puname').filter(lambda x: len(x) > 1)

    # adding markers with distinct colors for multiple outliers
    for _, row in highest_outliers.iterrows():
        is_multi_party = row['new_puname'] in multi_party_outliers['new_puname'].values
        color = 'white' if is_multi_party else party_colors[row['party']]
        outlier_parties = ', '.join([party.split('_')[0].upper() for party in highest_outliers[highest_outliers['new_puname'] == row['new_puname']]['party']])
        tooltip = f"Unit: {row['new_puname']}, Ward: {row['ward']}, Outliers: {outlier_parties}"

        folium.Marker(
            location=[row['Latitude'], row['Longitude']],
            tooltip=tooltip,
            icon=folium.Icon(color=color, icon='exclamation-sign')
        ).add_to(lagos_map)

# applying the outlier markers on dataframe
add_outlier_markers(location)
